    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-04T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-04T11:00:00-05:00" n="742"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.00/910: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-04T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 4, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4944. In talking with Mr. Eden this morning he told me that he hoped our
                    representative at Beirut in talking with General de Gaulle would discourage him
                    in an anti-British policy in Syria and the Lebanon.</p>
                <p>Mr. Eden also said that he understood Wadsworth<note n="66" xml:id="d742fn66"
                        >George Wadsworth, appointed American Diplomatic Agent and Consul General in
                        Syria and in Lebanon; for correspondence on this subject, see <ref
                            target="#pg_641">pp. 641</ref> ff.</note> is being sent to Beirut which
                    he very much approved and asked me if I would inquire how soon Wadsworth would
                    reach his destination.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
